# Operator service: cancel whichever BT goal is currently executing on
# /skill_server/execute_behavior_tree, regardless of which client started it.
#
# Why a service rather than the action's cancel handshake: rosbridge's
# action client must hold the goal id assigned at submit time to cancel it.
# Long-lived campaigns can outlive the browser session that started them
# (or the operator triggers cancel from a different machine), so the
# action-cancel path is unreachable. This service walks the BtExecutor's
# internal state and triggers the same halt path the goal-handle's
# cancel_callback does.

string reason
---
bool success
string message
string task_id           # the task that was cancelled (empty if none was active)
